The paper discusses recommender systems, which are commonly studied in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper touches on issues of fairness and balance, which are relevant to the sub-category of Cybersecurity and Privacy (cs.CY). The concept of multistakeholder recommendation also involves social and ethical considerations, which could fall under the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses the user experience and interface design, which could be relevant to the sub-category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
